HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 220
BY REPRESENTATIVE BILLINGS
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 5, 2026, as St. Charles Parish Day at the
state capitol
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as St. Charles Parish Day at the state capitol.
3 WHEREAS, St. Charles Parish is nestled along the banks of the Mississippi River
4 and located approximately twenty-five miles north of New Orleans; it is one of the original
5 nineteen parishes in the territory of Orleans and one of nine parishes in the New Orleans
6 metropolitan area; and
7 WHEREAS, St. Charles Parish is often referred to as part of the German coast
8 because of the large population of German farmers that settled in the area during the 1700s
9 and injected new life into the city of New Orleans; and
10 WHEREAS, St. Charles Parish is home to the St. Charles Parish Rotary Club's
11 Alligator Festival, and there are more than fifteen tourist attractions and fifteen fairs and
12 festivals in the parish each year; and
13 WHEREAS, Des Allemands and Lac des Allemands in St. Charles Parish are
14 renowned as "the catfish capital of the universe"; and
15 WHEREAS, St. Charles Parish has an abundance of resources, including catfish,
16 shrimp, crabs, natural gas, and oil, and is home to fourteen energy, petrochemical, and
17 logistic terminals and facilities; the parish is an economic force in southeast Louisiana and
18 accounts for nearly thirty percent of the total value of exports in the region.
19 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
20 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Tuesday, May 5, 2026, as St. Charles Parish
